inental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":10,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Sharpe was born in 1372, in Coggeshall, Essex, England, his father, Thomas Sharpe, was 22 and his mother, Clare Walden, was 18. He married Margaret Tey in 1396, in Coggeshall, Essex, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1400, in his hometown, at the age of 28."},"et":{"1372–1400":"1372–1400","1379–1400":"1379–1400","1400–1454":"1400–1454","1350–Male":"1350–Surnud","1355–1375":"1355–1375","1379":"1379","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1454":"1454","1375":"1375","1396":"1396","about 1400":"umbes 1400","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","after 1375":"pärast 1375","Coggeshall, Essex, England":"Coggeshall, Essex, England","of Maldon, Essex, England":"Coggeshall, Essex, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"1372–1400":"1372–1400","1379–1400":"1379–1400","1400–1454":"1400–1454","1350–Male":"1350–Kuollut","1355–1375":"1355–1375","1379":"1379","1400":"1400","1355":"1355","1454":"1454","1375":"1375","1396":"1396","about 1400":"noin 1400","1372":"1372","1350":"1350","1382":"1382","after 1375":"1375 jälkeen","Coggeshall, Essex